.TH "vmw_stdu_primary_plane_atomic_update" 9 "vmw_stdu_primary_plane_atomic_update" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_stdu_primary_plane_atomic_update \- formally switches STDU to new plane
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_stdu_primary_plane_atomic_update
.BI "(struct drm_plane *plane "  ","
.BI "struct drm_plane_state *old_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "plane" 12
display plane
.IP "old_state" 12
Only used to get crtc info
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Formally update stdu->display_srf to the new plane, and bind the new
plane STDU.  This function is called during the commit phase when
all the preparation have been done and all the configurations have
been checked.
